stories.text:
Hello HN. I did the big mistake of being signed in to my work Google account when I created my YouTube channel. The channel in question is my artist channel where i publish my music etc.

I didn't realize at the moment I created the channel, that I was signed in to my work account. And now I'm worried that I would lose access to this account one day if I where to get fired, quit etc.

I can't seem to find any way to transfer the channel to my private account. Is this just plain and simply impossible?
stories.title: Ask HN: Is it impossible to move a YouTube channel to different Google account?
